{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking tray, baking paper, cling film, large bowl, oven","id":"r341608","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-SI5jD_QrH0Q\/XZMvnjoaFuI\/AAAAAAAAaUM\/mwNncKf7X9kNBDl_f0TZmvZdWZ82KMiBACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lX_tef9I6n-oxRpx.png","title":"Tabbouleh-stuffed Peppers","publishedAt":"2019-03-04T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"70 g bulgar wheat (see tip)"},{"content":"120 g water, boiling"},{"content":"4 peppers, mixed"},{"content":"2 spring onions (approx. 35 g), cut in pieces (2 cm)"},{"content":"10 g fresh mint leaves"},{"content":"120 g fresh flat-leaf parsley, cut in pieces (2 cm)"},{"content":"200 g ripe tomatoes, quartered, deseeded"},{"content":"50 g extra virgin olive oil"},{"content":"1 lemon, finely grated zest and 30 g juice"},{"content":"1 tsp baharat spice mix (see tip) (optional)"},{"content":"½ tsp fine sea salt"},{"content":"¼ tsp ground black pepper"},{"content":"100 g cucumber, diced (5 mm)"},{"content":"80 g pomegranate seeds              (optional)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"14 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"23 g","calories":"1073 kJ \/ 258 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Preheat oven to 200°C and line a baking tray with baking paper."},{"content":"Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid then weigh in bulgar wheat and water. Cover with cling film and leave to soak for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, continue with recipe."},{"content":"Cut tops off peppers and discard. Remove pith and seeds from inside. Slice a little off the base so they sit flat but without making a hole. Place peppers on prepared tray, up side down, and bake for 15-20 minutes (200°C) until just softening. Meanwhile, make tabbouleh."},{"content":"Place spring onions, mint and 50 g parsley in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then chop again <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place remaining 70 g parsley in mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then chop again <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to bowl with herbs."},{"content":"Place tomatoes in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to bowl with herbs."},{"content":"Place oil, lemon zest, lemon juice, baharat (if using), salt and pepper in mixing bowl then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to bowl with herbs. When bulgar wheat has absorbed all the water, fluff with a fork to separate grains, add to bowl with herbs and stir well with spatula."},{"content":"Remove peppers from oven and carefully tip out any excess liquid. Divide tabbouleh mixture between peppers, filling each to the top. Bake for a further 10-15 minutes (200°C) until peppers are tender."},{"content":"Top peppers with cucumber and pomegranate seeds (if using) then serve warm or cold."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If bulgar wheat is not available, substitute with couscous and adjust quantity of water and soaking time in <b>step 2<b> according to packet instructions.","Baharat spice mix can be bought ready made or you can make your own. Place <b>1 Tbsp<b> black peppercorns, <b>1 Tbsp<b> coriander seeds, <b>1 Tbsp<b> cumin seeds, <b>½ Tbsp<b> allspice, <b>½ Tbsp<b> ground nutmeg, <b>1 tsp<b> ground sweet paprika, <b>½ tsp<b> cardamom seeds, <b>¼ tsp<b> whole cloves and <b>2 cinnamon<b> sticks then grind <b><b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>.<b> Store remaining baharat in an airtight container and add a pinch to soups and sauces or use as a rub on fish or meat.","Can be served as a starter or side dish."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","50m","4 pieces"]}